cssc3175

Files Included:
simarm.c
Makefile
README

Program Description:
This program simulates three disk arm scheduling algorithms:

1. FCFS - First Come, First Served
2. SSTF - Shortest Seek Time First
3. SCAN - Elevator algorithm

The program generates a random sequence of cylinder numbers from 0 to 999.
The user provides the length of the sequence as a command-line argument.
The program then calculates and prints the total distance traveled by the disk
arm for each scheduling algorithm.

SCAN Assumption:
The SCAN algorithm moves upward first toward larger cylinder numbers. If there
are requests below the starting position, the arm continues to cylinder 999,
then reverses direction and services the lower requests.

Compilation:
Run the following command inside the a3 directory:

make

This creates the executable named:

simarm

Execution:
Run the program with one positive integer argument:

./simarm 64

Example:
./simarm 64

Cleaning:
To remove object files and the executable, run:

make clean

Notes:
The program does not use the system() function.
The program is written in C and compiles cleanly with gcc.
